Analysis Reproducibility
========================

This directory contains reproducible code for the speed/accuracy analysis
in the SuperSNEC paper (Fremling et al.).

Prerequisites
-------------

- Python >= 3.10
- numpy, scipy, matplotlib, Pillow

Install with:  pip install numpy scipy matplotlib Pillow

Layout
------

scripts/    Python drivers for parameter sweeps, metrics, plots, and tables.
            Each sweep script is self-contained: runs SNEC, writes TSV results,
            AND generates its own LaTeX table(s).
results/    TSV snapshots from completed sweeps.
figures/    Generated analysis figures.

Pipeline Mapping
----------------

Table  Script                                    Output (.tex)
-----  ------                                    -------------
1      run_imax_scaling_scan.py                   table_imax_scaling
2      run_cumulative_speedup.py                  table_cumulative_speedup
3      run_adaptive_threshold_limits.py           table_solver_itmax_only
4      run_adaptive_threshold_limits.py           table_solver_epstol_only
5      run_imax_scaling_scan.py                   table_quad_convergence
6      run_ni_cadence_grid_mode_comparison.py     table_ni_cadence_comparison
7      run_remap_scheduling_sweep.py              table_remap_scheduling
8      run_legacy_ni_cadence_2d_sweep.py          table_legacy_ni_cadence

All tables are written to Paper/generated/.

One-command Rebuild
-------------------

  python3 Analysis/scripts/rebuild_all.py

Runs all sweep scripts (producing TSV results and LaTeX tables),
generates figures, and builds Paper/adaptive_gridding_for_snec.pdf.

Skip SNEC runs and regenerate tables from cached data:

  python3 Analysis/scripts/rebuild_all.py --skip-sweeps --skip-pdf

Each sweep script is called with --tables-only, reading cached TSV results
and regenerating LaTeX tables without re-running SNEC.

Regenerate Tables Only
----------------------

Each sweep script supports --tables-only:

  python3 Analysis/scripts/run_imax_scaling_scan.py --tables-only
  python3 Analysis/scripts/run_adaptive_threshold_limits.py --tables-only
  python3 Analysis/scripts/run_ni_cadence_grid_mode_comparison.py --tables-only
  python3 Analysis/scripts/run_remap_scheduling_sweep.py --tables-only
  python3 Analysis/scripts/run_legacy_ni_cadence_2d_sweep.py --tables-only

Regenerate Figures
------------------

  python3 Analysis/scripts/plot_adaptive_runtime_validation.py
  python3 Analysis/scripts/plot_lc_comparison_sne.py

Outputs are written under Analysis/figures/.
